    <p>
        <em> <alert>Separable Equations</alert> </em>
    </p>
    A first-order differential equation of the form <m>\dfrac{dy}{dx}=g(x)h(y)</m> is said to be <em> </em>.
    <p>
    </p>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Solve <m>(1+x)\dfrac{dy}{dx}-y=0</m>.
                Find the explicit solution.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </example>

    <p>
    </p>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Solve the initial value problem <m>\dfrac{dy}{dx}=-\dfrac{x}{y},</m> <m>y(4)=-3.</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </example>

    <p>
    </p>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Solve <m>(e^{2y}-y)\cos x \dfrac{dy}{dx}= e^{y} \sin 2x,</m> <m>y(0)=0.</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </example>

    <p>
    </p>

